juniLogMIB.name: juniLogMIB

revisions.description: Replaced Unisphere names with Juniper names.
Replace single syslog destination with table of syslog destinations, and add syslog facility as an attribute for syslogs.
Initial version of this MIB module.

juniLogMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@Juniper.net
juniLogMIB.description: The Logging Facility MIB for the Juniper Networks enterprise.

JuniLogCatName.name: JuniLogCatName
JuniLogCatName.description: The name of a log category. Represents textual information taken from the NVT ASCII character set.
JuniLogCatName.reference: RFC 854: NVT ASCII character set. See SNMPv2-TC.DisplayString DESCRIPTION for a summary.

JuniLogVerbosity.name: JuniLogVerbosity
JuniLogVerbosity.description: The log verbosity level. Not all event types offer medium- or high-verbosity levels of detail.

juniLogDestSyslogSeverity.name: juniLogDestSyslogSeverity
juniLogDestSyslogSeverity.description: The minimum severity level of messages sent to the SYSLOG server. A value of 'off' indicates no log messages are sent to this destination.

juniLogDestSyslogAddress.name: juniLogDestSyslogAddress
juniLogDestSyslogAddress.description: The IP address of the SYSLOG server to which log messages are to be sent. A value of 0.0.0.0 indicates no server address is configured.

juniLogSyslogTable.name: juniLogSyslogTable
juniLogSyslogTable.description: A table describing the characteristics of each syslog destination.

juniLogSyslogEntry.name: juniLogSyslogEntry
juniLogSyslogEntry.description: An entry describingthe characteristics of a syslog destination.

juniLogSyslogIpAddress.name: juniLogSyslogIpAddress
juniLogSyslogIpAddress.description: The IP address of this syslog destination. This value must be a unicast IP address.

juniLogSyslogRowStatus.name: juniLogSyslogRowStatus
juniLogSyslogRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table. Only 'createAndGo' and 'destroy' are supported.

juniLogSyslogSeverity.name: juniLogSyslogSeverity
juniLogSyslogSeverity.description: The severity level for this syslog destination. Setting this value to 'off' suppresses log messages from being sent to this syslog destination.

juniLogSyslogFacility.name: juniLogSyslogFacility
juniLogSyslogFacility.description: The facility id attached to messages sent to this syslog destination.

juniLogDestConsoleSeverity.name: juniLogDestConsoleSeverity
juniLogDestConsoleSeverity.description: The minimum severity level of messages sent to the console. A value of 'off' indicates no log messages are sent to this destination.

juniLogDestNvFileSeverity.name: juniLogDestNvFileSeverity
juniLogDestNvFileSeverity.description: The minimum severity level of messages sent to the nonvolatile log file. A value of 'off' indicates no log messages are to be sent to this destination.

juniLogCatTable.name: juniLogCatTable
juniLogCatTable.description: A table describing the characteristics of each log category.

juniLogCatEntry.name: juniLogCatEntry
juniLogCatEntry.description: An entry describing the characteristics of a log category.

juniLogCatIndex.name: juniLogCatIndex
juniLogCatIndex.description: An integer index uniquely associated with a log. Index values do not necessarily persist across system reboots. Following reboot, mappings of (reboot-invariant) log category names to log index values is available in the juniLogCatNameTable.

juniLogCatName.name: juniLogCatName
juniLogCatName.description: The name of this log category.

juniLogCatDescr.name: juniLogCatDescr
juniLogCatDescr.description: A description of the functionality for which events are recorded by this log category.

juniLogCatEngineering.name: juniLogCatEngineering
juniLogCatEngineering.description: An indication of whether this log is intended mainly for engineering development and debug purposes.

juniLogCatDiscards.name: juniLogCatDiscards
juniLogCatDiscards.description: The number of messages generated by this log category that were discarded because of resource limitations.

juniLogCatSeverity.name: juniLogCatSeverity
juniLogCatSeverity.description: The severity level for this log category. The value 'off' disables recording of this log category's messages. For other severity level values, only messages at or above this severity level will be logged in juniLogMsgTable.

juniLogCatVerbosity.name: juniLogCatVerbosity
juniLogCatVerbosity.description: The verbosity level for this log category. Supplementary information may be available for certain event types. This object controls whether that additional information, if available for a given event, is recorded.

juniLogCatNameTable.name: juniLogCatNameTable
juniLogCatNameTable.description: A table mapping each log category's name to its index.

juniLogCatNameEntry.name: juniLogCatNameEntry
juniLogCatNameEntry.description: An entry mapping a log category's name to its index.

juniLogCatNameName.name: juniLogCatNameName
juniLogCatNameName.description: The name of the log category.

juniLogCatNameIndex.name: juniLogCatNameIndex
juniLogCatNameIndex.description: The log index associated with this log category.

juniLogMsgCapacity.name: juniLogMsgCapacity
juniLogMsgCapacity.description: The maximum capacity, in number of log messages, of the juniLogMsgTable.

juniLogMsgLastSeqNumber.name: juniLogMsgLastSeqNumber
juniLogMsgLastSeqNumber.description: The sequence number of the most recent juniLogMsgTable entry. By monitoring this object's rate of change in relation to the juniLogMsgTable capacity, a management client can determine whether it is polling juniLogMsgTable frequently enough to avoid missing log messages.

juniLogMsgTable.name: juniLogMsgTable
juniLogMsgTable.description: A table of log messages generated by this device.

juniLogMsgEntry.name: juniLogMsgEntry
juniLogMsgEntry.description: A log message generated by this device.

juniLogMsgSysUpTimeStamp.name: juniLogMsgSysUpTimeStamp
juniLogMsgSysUpTimeStamp.description: The value of sysUpTime when this log message was recorded.

juniLogMsgSequenceNumber.name: juniLogMsgSequenceNumber
juniLogMsgSequenceNumber.description: A sequence number that uniquely identifies this entry. Sequence numbers are assigned consecutively beginning with 1. More recent entries have higher sequence numbers.

juniLogMsgCatName.name: juniLogMsgCatName
juniLogMsgCatName.description: Name of the log category that contributed this message.

juniLogMsgCatIndex.name: juniLogMsgCatIndex
juniLogMsgCatIndex.description: Index of the log category that contributed this message.

juniLogMsgText.name: juniLogMsgText
juniLogMsgText.description: The text of the log message. Truncation of log message text is indicated by n asterisk character ('*') in the last octet of a maximum-size string.

juniLogMsgDateAndTimeStamp.name: juniLogMsgDateAndTimeStamp
juniLogMsgDateAndTimeStamp.description: The date and time this message was generated.

juniLogMsgThreshold.name: juniLogMsgThreshold
juniLogMsgThreshold.description: Number of log messages which, when added to juniLogMsgTable, cause a juniLogMsgThresholdTrap to be generated. This value is expressed as a percentage of the capacity of juniLogMsgTable. A value of zero disables trap generation.

juniLogMsgThresholdTrap.name: juniLogMsgThresholdTrap
juniLogMsgThresholdTrap.description: This trap is generated to report that an incremental number of log messages (described by the value of juniLogMsgThreshold) have been added to juniLogMsgTable.

juniLogCompliance.name: juniLogCompliance
juniLogCompliance.description: Obsolete compliance statement for entities which implement the Juniper Networks Log MIB. This statement became obsolete when support for multiple SYSLOGs was added.

juniLogCompliance2.name: juniLogCompliance2
juniLogCompliance2.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Juniper Networks Log MIB, including support for multiple SYSLOG destinations.

juniLogGroup.name: juniLogGroup
juniLogGroup.description: Obsolete collection of objects providing management of Juniper Networks logging capabilities. This group became obsolete when support for multiple SYSLOGs was added.

juniLogGroup2.name: juniLogGroup2
juniLogGroup2.description: A collection of objects providing management of Juniper Networks logging capabilities, including support for multiple SYSLOG destinations.

juniLogTrapGroup.name: juniLogTrapGroup
juniLogTrapGroup.description: A management notification pertaining to logging operations.
